title: Make-up artist Jake Bailey found dead
text:
Celebrity make-up artist Jake Bailey, who was known for his work with singers Katy Perry, Selena Gomez and Paris Hilton has died at the age of 37 in Los Angeles.The LA County Coroner's office confirmed to eonline.com that Bailey was found in his car on Friday by his assistant and authorities believe he died from carbon monoxide poisoning. It appears Bailey left a note, but the coroner's office couldn't confirm to whom or how many notes were left. An autopsy is currently pending.
"It is with deep sadness that we share the news of Jake Bailey's passing," his agency, Starworks Artists, said in a statement. "He was an undeniable talent, a great friend, a loving son and brother, and our grief is shared with all those whose lives he's touched. The statement continued: "As one of the industry's most sought after make-up artists, Jake worked with an incredible client roster and his work has been featured in publications such as Vogue, Harper's Bazaar, Vogue Italia, Vanity Fair, and Allure. Bailey last posted on Instagram on Thursday, sharing a photo of himself without a caption.
